GulfTalent.com
Business Development Coordinator
Thomson Reuters
Dubai, UAE
Posted on: 1 May 2014
THE ROLE
Expand all
The purpose of this position is to support our Direct Sales team through generation and qualification of leads. This role requires working closely with the sales team to meet and exceed targets and objectives.
Key responsibilities:
- Create new opportunities for sales team and/or account managers by creating and filtering new target lists
- Drive demand in specific territories through focused telephone campaigns
- Cultivate leads by assessing the unique opportunities and laying out the value proposition for customers
- Conduct a needs analysis to meet the end users requirements
- Ensure consistent and ongoing coverage of account or territory assignments based on your understanding of your sales opportunities
- Understand all products and work closely with sales person
- Maintain the highest level of customer satisfaction within the accounts
- Maintain a positive, professional 'total customer service' attitude
- Coordinate, plan, and schedule sales meeting and demonstrations for the sales team
- Demonstrate the ability to create and manage conversations at all business and technical levels of a client's organization from their CEO to a Systems Administrator.
REQUIREMENTS
The following knowledge, skills and abilities may be acquired through a combination of formal schooling, self-education and prior related work experience.
- At least 2 years of experience in a successful telesales/inside sales role is mandatory
- Good communication skills in English are essential, in both written and oral form
- Cross-cultural sensitivity and ability to work in a multi-national environment
- Requires someone who is adaptable, and has the ability to use their initiative and problem-solving skills
ABOUT THE COMPANY
At Thomson Reuters, we believe what we do matters. We are passionate about our work, inspired by the impact it has on our business and our customers. As a team, we believe in winning as one - collaborating to reach shared goals, and developing through challenging and meaningful experiences. With over 60,000 employees in more than 100 countries, we work flexibly across boundaries and realize innovations that help shape industries around the world. Making this happen is a dynamic, evolving process, and we count on each employee to be a catalyst in driving our performance - and their own.
As a global business, we rely on diversity of culture and thought to deliver on our goals. To ensure we can do that, we seek talented, qualified employees in all our operations around the world regardless of race, color, sex/gender, including pregnancy, gender identity and expression, national origin, religion, sexual orientation, disability, age, marital status, citizen status, veteran status, or any other protected classification under country or local law. Thomson Reuters is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer providing a drug-free workplace.
